.TH NEDITOR 1 "June 2026" "Neditor v1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
neditor \- an advanced TUI text editor written completely in Nitpick

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B neditor
[\fIFILENAME\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B neditor
is a fast, extensible, and modal text editor built entirely using the Nitpick programming language.
It runs in standard terminals and uses ANSI escape codes to render its TUI and process keyboard and mouse input.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Modal Editing
Supports distinct modes for different tasks (Normal mode, Insert mode, Command mode, Search mode).
.TP
.B Mouse Support
Native terminal mouse tracking (click to move cursor, scroll wheel to scroll the viewport).
.TP
.B Terminal Resize Support (SIGWINCH)
Dynamically adapts its viewport when the terminal emulator window is resized.
.TP
.B Plugin System
Includes an extensible plugin architecture.

.SH KEYBINDINGS
.SS Normal Mode
.TP
.B h, j, k, l
Move cursor left, down, up, and right.
.TP
.B i
Enter Insert mode.
.TP
.B :
Enter Command mode.
.TP
.B /
Enter Search mode.
.TP
.B ctrl+s
Save the current file.
.TP
.B ctrl+q
Quit neditor.

.SS Insert Mode
.TP
.B ESC
Return to Normal mode.
.TP
.B Backspace
Delete character at the cursor.
.TP
.B Enter
Insert a newline.

.SS Command Mode
.TP
.B :w
Save file.
.TP
.B :q
Quit (can also use :wq to save and quit).
.TP
.B :s/foo/bar
Replace all occurrences of "foo" with "bar".

.SH BUGS
No known bugs. File loading may leak a tiny amount of string memory per file loaded due to language constraints, but this does not affect runtime stability.

